    <div class="equation-container">
        <h2>Ampere-Maxwell Equation</h2>
        <div class="equation">
            ∮ <b>B</b> · d<b>l</b> = μ<sub>0</sub> (I<sub>enc</sub> + ε<sub>0</sub> d/dt ∬ <b>E</b> · <b>n</b> da)
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="description">
        An <span class="highlight-red">electric current</span> or <span class="highlight-red">changing electric flux</span> through a 
        <span class="highlight-blue">surface</span> produces a circulating magnetic field around any boundary path.
    </div>


